'''Motard''': see [[supermoto]] n. [[French]] for biker, generally accepted term for a racing [[motorcycle]] designed to compete on tracks with pavement, dirt, and jump sections.  Popularized by the made-for-[[TV]] racing series "Superbikers", the French adopted the sport and used their own 'supermotard' term for it.  Many years later it has gained worldwide popularity, and is commonly called supermotard, motard, or supermoto.